# Creating a Struct

We define a Struct using the `struct` keyword, followed by a name (always Capitalized!), and curly braces `{ }`.

```swift
struct Player {
    // We will define what makes up a player inside here!
}
```
Right now, `Player` is just a blueprint. It's instructions on how to build a player. It isn't an actual player yet!
